item.title: I still havent fixed
item.dc:creator: @Trent1 Trent!!
item.description:
@Trent1 wrote:

[quote=“mmaKush, post:9, topic:307751”][quote author=justinxg27 link=topic=403902.msg2991813#msg2991813 date=1255317607]
Trent, you got to go into item.java and search ‘public static int gloves’ and add DClaws ID to this string,

[/quote]

You’re wrong, he’s not equipping gloves, he’s equipping a weapon…

To fix your model loading problem, you need to add the model to your Models folder, add the int in your Class8 class (non-renamed), and then log on in-game and do in these exact words,

“add model MODELID”.

Where I have MODELID put the models ID there, then restart your client and it should work, btw, don’t worry about adding it in Item.java because items that aren’t defined in Item.java automatically go to the weapons slot, just add it in your Item.cfg file to add the currency & bonuses.[/quote]

this is exactly what i have done numerous times.
i get the same thing EVERY time.
